      <h1>AWS EventBridge debuging</h1>
      <div class="meta">2024-11-29</div>
      <div class="body">After doing some research on the internet I discovered that the place to see the results of AWS EventBridge failures was the CloudTrail logs. Once I started digging in there I discovered that my exception was "Error retrieving subnet information for [1]: The subnet ID '1' does not exist (ErrorCode: InvalidSubnetID.NotFound)"
<img src="https://pub.cmh.sh/worker_cloudtrail_RunTask.png" alt="run task filtering"/></br>
So I went and edited the rule and cleaned up this error, and started cycling through all of my configuration issues. In the end I created a new SecurityGroup to allow traffic for the ECS containers, specifying the subnets it should use, and insured that it was setup to launch with fargate.
